I am Ahmed Hagag (IEEE Mโ13). I received a B.Sc. (Honours) degree in pure mathematics and computer science from the Faculty of Science, Menoufia University, Egypt, in 2008, and an M.Sc. degree in computer science from the same university, in 2013. I received my Ph.D. degree in computer science from the School of Computer Science and Technology, Harbin Institute of Technology, China, in 2017. In 2009, I joined the teaching staff at the Faculty of Computers and Information Technology, Egyptian E-Learning University, Cairo, Egypt, where I am currently a lecturer in the Faculty of Computers and Artificial Intelligence, Benha University. My current research interests include satellite-image processing, deep learning, remote sensing image interpretation, especially compression, classification, and wireless communication.
